Who was the alumni that taught at the school first, served as a tea server in 1925, had three paintings at the George Eastman hall of RIT, and also did the wall in Gosnell?<image 1>

A. Josef Albers
B. George Eastman
C. Gosnell Hall
D. Tea Server 1925

The correct answer is:

A. Josef Albers

Josef Albers was an influential artist and educator who taught at various institutions, including Black Mountain College and Yale University. He is known for his abstract geometric compositions, particularly his "Homage to the Square" series, which includes the image you provided. Albers also had a significant impact on art education and theory. The details about serving as a tea server in 1925, having paintings at the George Eastman Hall of RIT, and working on the wall in Gosnell are likely specific to his involvement with those institutions.
